snippet.textDisplay: আমি কি আর বলব, যতবার কোক স্টুডিওর গান শুনি ততবার আমি অবাক হই!প্রতিবার কোন না কোন গানের একটা বদল হতে দেখা যায়? অবশ্যই এর মধ্যে নতুনত্ব তো আছেই গানের মধ্যে কোন সন্দেহ নাই। আর, সবশেষে আমি যেটি পেয়েছি এর মধ্যে তাহল, এই গানের মধ্যে আঞ্চলিক, ভাটিয়ালি, ভাওয়াইয়া, ময়মনসিংহের গীতিকা, ক্লাসিক্যাল, রক, র‍্যাপ, রবীন্দ্র ও নজরুল সংগীত এবং লালন শাহ্ কে দেখলাম গানের শব্দচয়নে। [What else can I say, every time I listen to a Coke Studio song, I'm surprised! Every time there's a change in some song? Of course, there is no doubt that there is innovation in the song. And, the last thing I got was, this song includes regional, Bhatiali, Bhawaiya, Mymensingh Geetika, Classical, Rock, Rap, Rabindra and Nazrul Sangeet and I saw Lalon Shah in the lyrics.] ❤❤❤

snippet.textDisplay:
In this captivating fusion masterpiece, Hamida Banu's ethereal voice breathes life into the timeless verses of the legendary poet, composer, and philosopher, Hason Raja, as she sings "Dhoro Dilaram." Her melodious notes thread through the song, carrying the listener to a place where ancient wisdom and modern artistry blend seamlessly. The song's title can be loosely translated as "Hold My Heart."

It conveys a yearning to cleanse the heart and reach a higher state of consciousness. In Baul philosophy, "Dilaram" symbolizes the innermost self or soul, and the song's message centers on seeking a connection with the divine within.

Arnob, in his soulful rendition of "Amai Dhore Rakho," adds a contemporary touch to this symphonic journey. His lyrics resonate with longing and a heartfelt plea for connection.

The title, "Hold Me," carries lyrics that express deep longing, love, and a desire for emotional closeness. It conveys the message of wanting to be held and protected by someone dear. The lyrics touch on themes of emotional attachment, vulnerability, and a plea for reassurance and comfort.

However, this fusion transcends mere melody blending; it represents a metaphorical plea from Arnob to his cherished audience. Through every note and word, he implores his friends, well-wishers, and devoted listeners to hold him close, to keep him in the chambers of their hearts.

It serves as a poignant reminder of music's power to unite, evoke emotion, and forge lasting bonds.

In the realm of folk and mystical songs, interpretations are diverse, and individuals may discover personal and spiritual meanings in the lyrics.

snippet.textDisplay:
This song proves how great Arnob is both as a singer and a musician! I always wanted to watch him singing high notes, from coming out of his slow voice comfort zone.
I love how the song creates tension (from clarinet) and again plunges into calm phase. 
and man, the last two lines create such a hollow in the heart, it made me want to listen the "Amay Dhore Rakho" more.
Such a good song it is! Thank you CSB for giving Arnob the opportunity to create the magic that we wanted!
